## Code Style
- Use file-scoped namespaces
- Use primary constructors where appropriate
- Prefer `var` for obvious types
- Use expression-bodied members for single-line methods
- Nullable reference types enabled — handle nulls explicitly

## Patterns
- All controller actions must be async (return `Task<ActionResult<T>>` or `Task<IActionResult>`)
- Never use `Thread.Sleep` — always `await Task.Delay()`
- Validation failures must `return` the error response (not just call it)
- Service interfaces go in the same file as the interface definition
- Use CancellationToken on all async methods
- Use `TimeSpan` for timeout configuration, not raw integers

## Testing
- One test class per production class
- Use NSubstitute for mocking interfaces
- Test both happy path and error cases
- Name tests: MethodName_Condition_ExpectedResult

## Don'ts
- Don't nest model classes inside controllers
- Don't use `Newtonsoft.Json` — use `System.Text.Json`
- Don't catch generic `Exception` unless re-throwing
- Don't use static service locator patterns
